 as a light snack or for afternoon tea.","When making coconut butter, the time required may vary depending on the type of coconut used and the ambient room temperature. If the room is cold, the process may take longer.","Protein balls should be stored in the refrigerator, as coconut butter may melt in warmer temperatures."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","24 pieces"]}